Rajiv Gandhi was assassinated in 1991. The last of a political
dynasty, he was the best known of the those assassinated between 1988
and 1994. Lesser political figures met death in six other
countries. Three presidential candidates were killed in Columbia over
a nine-month period. A presidential candidate and another Mexican
politician were murdered. The second ranking official within the PLO
was assassinated in Tunisia.  Iraqi agents killed the leader of the
Egyptian parliament, and Abu-Nidal terrorists assassinated a Jordanian
diplomat in Lebanon. Communist rebels killed the Chief of Police in
Makati, a city in the Philippines.</SUM>
